When writing a tech blog, a single line of code is worth a thousand words. By using the <%= link_to "highlight gem", "https://github.com/simplabs/highlight" %> and a bit of css trick, you can have a colorful code section in your rails app page as below. 
<%= link_to article_path(article) do %>
	Read More <i class="icon-signin"></i>
<% end %>
<% code = "class ArticlesController < ApplicationController
  # GET /articles/1
  # GET /articles/1.json
  def show
    @article = Article.find(params[:id])

    respond_to do |format|
      format.html # show.html.erb
      format.json { render json: @article }
    end
  end
end" %>
<%= render 'code_section', :title => "/path/to/your/class.rb", :code => code, :lang => :rb %>